text: is a town located in Okhotsk Subprefecture, Hokkaido, Japan. As of September 2016, the town has an estimated population of 5,011 and a population density of 7 persons per km². The total area is 716.60 km². ==History== *1919: Tsubetsu Village founded, split from Bihoro Village (now Town). *1921: Part of Bihoro Village incorporated. *1946: Tsubetsu Village becomes Tsubetsu Town. ==External links== * *Official Website Category:Towns in Hokkaido
title: Tsubetsu, Hokkaido
